                <mxCell id="FRtwtoELSkMl5iPatHwE-0" value="&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;1. GitHub Pipelines publishes artifacts in both regions&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Artifacts are registered with local ARNs as Targets&lt;br&gt;2. Aliases and Schedules are saved to Dynamo Global&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; Tables, without region-specific data&lt;br&gt;3. On DR Event, Route 53 is pointed to new active&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; region&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(63, 63, 63);&quot;&gt;4. Resync Lambda recreates EB schedules based on&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; the state in the Global Tables for the Aliases&lt;br&gt;5. Aliases work with the new ARNs because targets&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; are&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;maintained.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=#666666;fillColor=#f5f5f5;align=left;verticalAlign=top;whiteSpace=wrap;rounded=1;fontSize=10;fontColor=#333333;" parent="a0mG_4TwkRaPmkDLh-Au-0" vertex="1">
